<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Frame</strong>:</td><td>10 Years</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mechanical Parts:</strong></td><td>3 Years</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Electronics</strong>:</td><td>3 Years</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Labor</strong>:</td><td>1 Year</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"100%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"verticalAlignment\":\"center\",\"width\":\"\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":188,\"aspectRatio\":\"1\",\"scale\":\"cover\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost:10011/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/BFBXT8J.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-188\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1;object-fit:cover\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Return Policy</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>30 days to return or exchange</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Product must be unopened</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Customer Reviews:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4/5 Stars:</strong> Bluetooth only works with paid jrny app.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Verified Buyer Reviewed by Kiki- March 12, 2025</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Bluetooth set up was very confusing and not well explained in manual. My phone recognized the treadmill but asked for a pairing code which I never did locate from any official source. A reddit thread of others complaining about the same issue offered a suggested code that finally worked. However only the jrny app could be paired. It\'s unfortunate the built in speakers cannot be used with music apps or other non jrny app features. That was not explained in any promotional information. You have to pay to use the Bluetooth or speakers, which doesn\'t seem right.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Treadmills','','publish','closed','closed','','treadmills','','','2025-03-14 06:27:55','2025-03-14 06:27:55','',0,'http://localhost:10011/?page_id=45',0,'page','',0);
